.TH "signal_delivered" 9 "signal_delivered" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
signal_delivered \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" signal_delivered
.BI "(struct ksignal *ksig "  ","
.BI "int stepping "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ksig" 12
kernel signal struct
.IP "stepping" 12
nonzero if debugger single-step or block-step in use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function should be called when a signal has successfully been
delivered. It updates the blocked signals accordingly (\fIksig->ka.sa.sa_mask\fP
is always blocked, and the signal itself is blocked unless SA_NODEFER
is set in \fIksig->ka.sa.sa_flags\fP.  Tracing is notified.
